Raja SA, a water utility on the
 Black Sea  in  Romania â€™s Constanta county, is seeking bids to
upgrade about 56 million lei ($16 million) of water and sewage
systems, a European Union procurement  document  showed.  Raja plans to rehabilitate and extend waste collection and
upgrade a wastewater pump station in the city of Constanta for
32.3 million lei. Bids must be submitted by Nov. 5.  The company also plans to extend and upgrade water and
wastewater systems in Ialomita county west of Constanta for
about 23.7 million lei. Bids must be submitted by Nov. 11.  To contact the reporter on this story:
